## XES Mapping

```xml
<!-- Each git commit becomes an XES event -->
<event>
  <string key="concept:name" value="feat"/>       <!-- git:commitType label -->
  <string key="git:scope"    value="prediction"/> <!-- conventional commit scope -->
  <string key="git:sha"      value="8a20902"/>    <!-- short SHA -->
  <string key="org:resource" value="dev@example.com"/> <!-- git:author -->
  <date   key="time:timestamp" value="2026-04-06T01:29:06Z"/>
</event>
```

## Process Mining Predictions from Git History

| Prediction Target | Interpretation |
|------------------|----------------|
| `remaining_time` | Time until next release tag |
| `next_activity`  | Most likely next commit type after current sequence |
| `outcome`        | Will this PR merge (normal) or close without merge? |

## OTel Attributes

Spans emitted during git event ingestion use these attributes from the weaver registry:

- `git.commit.sha` — short SHA-1
- `git.commit.type` — maps to XES `concept:name`
- `git.commit.scope` — conventional commit scope
- `git.commit.is_breaking` — breaking change flag
- `git.branch.name` — XES case identifier
- `github.pr.number` — XES case:id for PR-scoped analysis
- `github.pr.state` — XES lifecycle:transition value
- `github.pr.cycle_time_ms` — duration attribute

